dversarial phase without code changes.\n\n## Implication for adversary-class design\n\nThe `LinearDynamicsAdversary` (Î”AÂ·x, 5 PGD inner steps, eta_max=0.1) saturated its Frobenius-norm ceiling for both linear architectures â€” meaning the adversary was operating at its expressive limit. Stronger adversary classes (full-state Îµ per `d448c9d` plan) may produce different signatures. For now, the practical training-method takeaway is that the linear-architecture / standard-adversary combination produces uniform +78% inflation.\n\nSee `410d7ac` for the full MVP report.","files":null}]}